    1575 CEAD Complex, unsymmetric eigenvalue analysis or singular value decomposition Main Index Given that [M], [B] and [K] are mass, damping, and stiffness, solve the equation: ([M] p2 + [B] p + [K]){ } = 0 (4-3) or {L}T ([M] p2 + [B] p + [K]) = {0} (Lanczos only) (4-4) for the eigenvalues p and the associated right eigenvectors {} or left eigenvectors {L}.     CKORTHO Check if a matrix has only diagonal terms1580 Main Index Check if a matrix has only diagonal terms. Format: Input Data Block: Output Data Block: None Parameters: Method: CKORTHO simply reads in the columns of the matrix and checks first to see that there are non-zero terms on the diagonal, then checks any off-diagonal terms to see if they are greater than the diagonal term/OFFRATIO.     1581 CLEANVEC Find and identify potential repeated roots in normal modes Main Index Search the eigenvalue table for potential repeated roots and, if found, identify them. Format: Input Data Block: Output Data Block: Parameters: Method: CLEANVEC begins by setting FRSTMODE to 0, it then searches starting with the MODENO eigenvalue for potential repeated roots. When looking at a mode, if the eigenvalue of the next mode is less than the eigenvalue of the current mode*(1+TOL/100.) then it is considered to be a repeated root and (if FRSTMODE=0, then FRSTMODE is set to the mode number of the current mode). The module then continues comparing eigenvalues until one does not satisfy the criteria to be considered a repeated root of the current set. At that point, MODENO is set to the highest mode in the set. The process of comparing eigenvalues is continued until either a mode which doesn’t satisfy the criteria is found or the last mode has been checked.CLEANVEC Find and identify potential repeated roots in normal modes CLEANVEC EIGMAT/PARTVEC/DOIT/TOL/ZERO/S,N,FRSTMODE/ S,N,MODENO/S,N,EIGENVAL $ EIGMAT Matrix with eigenvalues in it. PARTVEC Partition vector with 1.0 for the current set of potential repeated roots. DOIT Input-character-default=‘NO’. Flag determining whether the module performs the check or not. TOL Input-real-default=0.01. T olerance in percent used to determine whether roots are potential repeated roots. ZERO Input-real-default = 0.0001. Frequency (Hz) considered to be 0.0Hz. FRSTMODE Output-integer-default=0 - number of first mode identified as a potential repeated root. MODENO Input/output-integer-default=-1 - if input as positive, it is the last repeated root found in previous calls to the module. As output, it is the number of potential repeated roots in the current set. If set to -1 then no potential repeated roots were found. EIGENVAL Output-real-default=0.0 - eigenvalue of the set of potential repeated roots.
